ural landscapes, in particular where natural edge habitats are missing, compared to our natural control. The current trend in conversion of natural habitat in favour of macadamia monocultures, especially if remnant natural patches at orchard boundaries are removed, will have widespread detrimental effects on bat diversity. The resulting reduced biological pest suppression by bats and increased reliance on chemical control may further exacerbate biodiversity declines.", "access_right": "restricted", "creators": [{"name": "Weier, Sina M.", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Linden, Valerie M.G.", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Hammer, Antonia", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Grass, Ingo", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Tscharntke, Teja", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Taylor, Peter J.", "affiliation": null}], "keywords": ["Biodiversity", "Mammalia", "Chiroptera", "Chordata", "Animalia", "bats", "bat"], "related_identifiers": [{"identifier": "hash://md5/d0a9ce57cc4b16db6e505c28ebbf0d77", "relation": "hasVersion", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "hash://sha256/2cb94cf15549a800cdb40b6ad40d2177e6b85c8332ee50000741ef06a3b3d013", "relation": "hasVersion", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "zotero://select/groups/5435545/items/AWTLTCVE", "relation": "isDerivedFrom", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "https://zotero.org/groups/5435545/items/AWTLTCVE", "relation": "isDerivedFrom", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "https://linker.bio/cut:hash://md5/6785bfeb7172bbd2b0303e13d2f77fa3!/b44319-46780", "relation": "isDerivedFrom", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "hash://md5/330417efcaa2560c9b8ebcd6fae17ce0", "relation": "isPartOf", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "10.5281/zenodo.1410543", "relation": "isCompiledBy", "resource_type": "software", "scheme": "doi"}], "custom": {"dwc:class": ["Mammalia"], "dwc:kingdom": ["Animalia"], "dwc:order": ["Chiroptera"], "dwc:phylum": ["Chordata"]}, "resource_type": {"title": "Journal article", "type": "publication", "subtype": "article"}, "jour